***Notes for GST 101 from Canvas***
***Module 1***
***QGIS 2.14 Essen***

Absolute space:  mathematical space
Topological space:  relative space (EX:  metrorail maps where the stops are evenly spaced out. Not true in real life).
Cognitive space:  people's beliefs, experiences, and perceptions about places

Location:  absolute, relative, nominal, cognitive.
  absolute: latitude/longitude // unambiguous
  relative: site and situation
  cognitive: place name
  nominal: "where were you when...?"
  
  First law of geography:  "Everything is related to everything else, but near things are more related to each other,"
    Waldo Tobler
      Relative and cognitive relationships have an influence
      
